const o="02",n={en:"Existing Scholarship and Academic Resources on Christianity in Vietnam",vi:"Học thuật và tài nguyên nghiên cứu hiện có về Kitô giáo tại Việt Nam"},i={en:"The academic study of Christianity in Vietnam draws on multiple scholarly traditions -- French colonial historiography, Vietnamese-language church history, English-language social history, and theological reflection from the Vietnamese diaspora. This report maps the major scholars, works, archives, journals, and institutions that define the field, and identifies critical gaps in English-language access that affect missions planning and strategy.",vi:"Việc nghiên cứu học thuật về Kitô giáo tại Việt Nam dựa trên nhiều truyền thống học thuật -- sử học thuộc địa Pháp, lịch sử giáo hội bằng tiếng Việt, lịch sử xã hội bằng tiếng Anh, và suy tư thần học từ cộng đồng hải ngoại Việt Nam. Báo cáo này lập bản đồ các học giả, tác phẩm, lưu trữ, tạp chí và tổ chức chính định hình lĩnh vực này, và xác định những khoảng trống quan trọng trong tiếp cận tiếng Anh. [Bản dịch AI — Chờ xem xét]"},e=["scholarship","archives","history"],t=14,a=!1,s=JSON.parse(`[{"heading":{"en":"Major Western Scholars and Works","vi":"Các học giả phương Tây và tác phẩm chính"},"content":{"en":"### Charles Keith\\n\\nCharles Keith (Michigan State University) authored *Catholic Vietnam: A Church from Empire to Nation* (UC Press, 2012), the most important single English-language monograph on Vietnamese Catholicism. Keith demonstrates how French colonial rule transformed Catholic missions into powerful institutional structures, and how Vatican reforms enabling an independent national Church allowed Vietnamese Catholics to redefine their relationships with both missionary Catholicism and colonial rule.\\n\\n### Peter C. Phan\\n\\nPeter C. Phan (Georgetown University), a Vietnamese-born theologian, is the most prolific Vietnamese-American scholar of Christianity. He has authored or edited over 30 books and 300+ essays. Key works include *Vietnamese-American Catholics* (2005), *Asian Christianities* (2018), and *The Joy of Religious Pluralism* (2017). He is the first non-Anglo president of the Catholic Theological Society of America.\\n\\n### Jacob Ramsay\\n\\nJacob Ramsay authored *Mandarins and Martyrs* (Stanford, 2008), challenging the conventional narrative that blames French missionaries for destabilizing dynastic Vietnam, arguing for a more complex account of anti-Catholicism shaped by grassroots religious dynamics.\\n\\n### Keith Taylor\\n\\nKeith Taylor (Cornell University) published *A History of the Vietnamese* (Cambridge, 2013), a comprehensive narrative addressing religion within the broader sweep of Vietnamese history.\\n\\n### Older French-Language Works\\n\\n**Georges Taboulet** compiled *La Geste Francaise en Indochine* (1956), a two-volume, 937-page documentary history covering French engagement from its origins through 1914, including primary documents on Jesuit evangelization, MEP activity, and anti-Christian edicts.","vi":"### Charles Keith\\n\\n*Catholic Vietnam: A Church from Empire to Nation* (2012) là chuyên khảo tiếng Anh quan trọng nhất về Công giáo Việt Nam.\\n\\n### Peter C. Phan\\n\\nHọc giả gốc Việt nhiều tác phẩm nhất về Kitô giáo, với hơn 30 cuốn sách và 300 bài luận.\\n\\n### Jacob Ramsay\\n\\n*Mandarins and Martyrs* (2008) đưa ra cách nhìn phức tạp hơn về chống Công giáo dưới triều Nguyễn."}},{"heading":{"en":"Vietnamese-Language Scholarship","vi":"Học thuật bằng tiếng Việt"},"content":{"en":"### Church Historians Writing in Vietnamese\\n\\nA substantial body of Vietnamese-language church history exists but remains poorly indexed and largely inaccessible to English-speaking researchers. **Nguyen Hong** authored *Lich su truyen giao o Viet Nam* (History of Evangelization in Vietnam), one of the foundational works. Parish histories, diocesan records, and seminary theses produced inside Vietnam contain granular data unavailable elsewhere but are rarely catalogued in Western academic databases.\\n\\n### Seminary-Based Research\\n\\nVietnam's major seminaries are active centers of theological education:\\n\\n- **Saint Sulpice Major Seminary, Hue** (est. 1740) -- the oldest in Vietnam\\n- **Saint Joseph Major Seminary, Ho Chi Minh City** (est. 1860) -- currently trains approximately 300 seminarians\\n- **Saint Joseph Major Seminary, Hanoi** (est. 1932)\\n\\nThe training follows an eight-year curriculum. Vietnam has one of the highest numbers of seminarians in Asia, with about 20 new priests ordained yearly in the Hanoi archdiocese alone.","vi":"### Các nhà sử học giáo hội viết bằng tiếng Việt\\n\\nNhiều tài liệu lịch sử giáo hội bằng tiếng Việt tồn tại nhưng khó tiếp cận với người nghiên cứu nói tiếng Anh. **Nguyễn Hồng** viết *Lịch sử truyền giáo ở Việt Nam*, một trong những công trình nền tảng."}},{"heading":{"en":"Key Journals and Publications","vi":"Các tạp chí và ấn phẩm chính"},"content":{"en":"### English-Language Journals\\n\\n- **Studies in World Christianity** (Edinburgh University Press, est. 1995)\\n- **International Journal of Asian Christianity (IJAC)** (Brill) -- multidisciplinary journal particularly relevant for contemporary Vietnamese Christianity\\n- **Journal of World Christianity** (Penn State University Press)\\n- **International Journal for the Study of the Christian Church** -- has published Vietnam-specific articles\\n\\n### French-Language Journals\\n\\n- **Revue d'histoire des missions** -- historical journal of Catholic missions with archival articles on Indochina\\n- **Persee.fr** -- French open-access platform hosting multiple articles on missionary activity in Tonkin, Annam, and Cochinchina\\n- **Cairn.info** -- hosts recent French-language scholarship on Catholicism, Buddhism, and secular laws in Tonkin","vi":"### Tạp chí tiếng Anh\\n\\n- **Studies in World Christianity**, **IJAC** (Brill), **Journal of World Christianity** và nhiều tạp chí khác đã xuất bản nghiên cứu về Kitô giáo Việt Nam.\\n\\n### Tạp chí tiếng Pháp\\n\\n- **Persee.fr** và **Cairn.info** là nền tảng truy cập mở quan trọng cho nghiên cứu thời thuộc địa."}},{"heading":{"en":"Research Centers and Institutions","vi":"Trung tâm nghiên cứu và tổ chức"},"content":{"en":"### IRFA (Institut de recherche France-Asie)\\n\\nFounded in 2019 by the Missions Etrangeres de Paris, IRFA is the single most important institutional resource for French Catholic missions in Asia. Holdings include 800 linear meters of unpublished archives in French, Latin, and ~30 Asian languages; 500 printed works in Central Vietnamese ethnic group languages; and 20,000 volumes.\\n\\n### Georgetown University\\n\\nGeorgetown's Berkley Center houses Peter Phan's work and hosts conferences on Asian Christianity.\\n\\n### SOAS, London\\n\\nSOAS's Centre of World Christianity supports research on Christianity in Southeast Asia, including work on Protestant Christianity among Hmong communities.\\n\\n### Other Institutions\\n\\n- **Cornell University** -- Keith Taylor's program; strong Vietnamese-language holdings\\n- **University of Bonn** -- 2021 dissertation on Hmong Protestant religious life\\n- **Loyola School of Theology, Philippines** -- trains Vietnamese Jesuits\\n- **Santa Clara University** -- multiple recent dissertations on Vietnamese Catholic topics","vi":"### IRFA\\n\\nThành lập năm 2019 bởi MEP, IRFA là nguồn tài nguyên tổ chức quan trọng nhất với 800 mét dài lưu trữ chưa xuất bản.\\n\\n### Các tổ chức khác\\n\\nGeorgetown, SOAS London, Cornell, Đại học Bonn và Santa Clara đều có chương trình nghiên cứu liên quan."}},{"heading":{"en":"Primary Source Collections","vi":"Các bộ sưu tập nguồn sơ cấp"},"content":{"en":"### MEP Archives\\n\\nThe MEP archives, now housed at IRFA in Paris, constitute the richest primary source collection for Vietnamese Christianity history. They contain correspondence, missionary letters, reports, financial records, and grammars spanning from the seventeenth through twentieth centuries.\\n\\n### Vatican Archives (Propaganda Fide)\\n\\nThe historical archives contain mission finances, reports from Vatican envoys, and the landmark 1659 *Instructio* --- the \\"Magna Carta of the missions\\" directing missionaries to develop indigenous clergy and adapt to local culture.\\n\\n### French Colonial Archives (ANOM)\\n\\nArchives nationales d'outre-mer in Aix-en-Provence hold repatriated colonial records providing the state perspective on church-colonial dynamics.\\n\\n### Alexandre de Rhodes' Writings\\n\\nTwo foundational texts: the **Dictionarium Annamiticum Lusitanum et Latinum** (1651) --- the first trilingual dictionary codifying chu Quoc ngu --- and the **Catechismus** (1651) in Vietnamese using the Quoc ngu script. These are among the most important primary sources for both early Vietnamese Christianity and the history of the Vietnamese language.","vi":"### Lưu trữ MEP\\n\\nLưu trữ MEP tại IRFA Paris là bộ sưu tập nguồn sơ cấp phong phú nhất. Lưu trữ Vatican và ANOM bổ sung góc nhìn từ nhà nước. Các tác phẩm của Alexandre de Rhodes là nguồn sơ cấp quan trọng nhất cho giai đoạn đầu."}},{"heading":{"en":"Dissertations and Recent Research","vi":"Luận văn và nghiên cứu gần đây"},"content":{"en":"### PhD Dissertations\\n\\n- **Le Hoang Phu** (NYU, 1972) -- *A Short History of the Evangelical Church of Vietnam (1911--1965)*. At 560 pages, this remains the most comprehensive English-language study of Vietnamese Protestantism.\\n- **University of Bonn** (2021) -- Dissertation on Hmong Protestant religious life in the Central Highlands.\\n- **Santa Clara University** -- Recent dissertations on Vietnamese Catholic Christological discipleship, death and afterlife among Vietnamese-American Catholics, and Catholic-Buddhist interfaith marriage.\\n\\n### Recent Journal Articles (2020--2026)\\n\\n- \\"Protestantism among the Hmong People in Northern Vietnam\\" (*Religions*, MDPI, 2024)\\n- \\"Hmong Christianisation, the Will to Improve and Neoliberalism in Vietnam's Highlands\\" (*European Journal of East Asian Studies*, Brill, 2021)\\n- \\"Alternative Development Trajectories? Religion as a Vector of Mobility among the Hmong\\" (*Journal of Rural Studies*, 2023)\\n\\nThe emerging trend is a significant increase in social-scientific research on ethnic minority Protestantism --- a contrast to the historically Catholic-dominated field.","vi":"### Luận văn tiến sĩ\\n\\nLuận văn của **Lê Hoàng Phủ** (NYU, 1972) vẫn là nghiên cứu toàn diện nhất bằng tiếng Anh về đạo Tin Lành Việt Nam. Xu hướng gần đây là nghiên cứu khoa học xã hội về đạo Tin Lành dân tộc thiểu số tăng đáng kể."}},{"heading":{"en":"Gaps in English-Language Access","vi":"Khoảng trống trong tiếp cận tiếng Anh"},"content":{"en":"### What Exists Only in Vietnamese\\n\\nNguyen Hong's foundational church history, parish histories, diocesan records, seminary theses, and Vietnamese Catholic periodicals remain unavailable in English.\\n\\n### What Exists Only in French\\n\\nTaboulet's *La Geste Francaise*, the bulk of MEP correspondence, and important articles on Persee.fr and Cairn.info have never been translated.\\n\\n### Structural Gaps\\n\\n- **Protestant scholarship is thin.** The CMA's 100+ year presence has produced remarkably little academic history beyond Le Hoang Phu's 1972 dissertation.\\n- **Post-1975 church life is under-documented.** The period from reunification to present lacks comprehensive English-language treatment.\\n- **Ethnic minority Christianity needs more work.** Christianity among highland groups beyond the Hmong remains under-studied.\\n- **Vietnamese seminary research is inaccessible** to international databases.\\n\\n### Implications for Missions Research\\n\\nEnglish-speaking missions organizations are operating with an incomplete picture. Priority translation targets include Nguyen Hong's mission history, selected MEP materials, and recent Vietnamese-language seminary research.","vi":"### Những gì chỉ có bằng tiếng Việt hoặc tiếng Pháp\\n\\nNhiều tài liệu nền tảng chưa được dịch sang tiếng Anh, tạo ra bất lợi cấu trúc cho các tổ chức truyền giáo nói tiếng Anh."}}]`),r={id:"02",title:n,summary:i,tags:e,readingTime:t,featured:a,sections:s};export{r as default,a as featured,o as id,t as readingTime,s as sections,i as summary,e as tags,n as title};
